  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for postgresql18",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for postgresql18 fixes the following issues:\n\n- Update to version 18.3. (bsc#1258754)\n- CVE-2026-2003: Guard against unexpected dimensions of oidvector/int2vector (bsc#1258008)\n- CVE-2026-2004: Harden selectivity estimators against being attached to operators that accept unexpected data types. (bsc#1258009)\n- CVE-2026-2005: Fix buffer overrun in contrib/pgcrypto's PGP decryption functions. (bsc#1258010)\n- CVE-2026-2006: Fix inadequate validation of multibyte character lengths. (bsc#1258011)\n- CVE-2026-2007: Harden contrib/pg_trgm against changes in string lowercasing behavior. (bsc#1258012)\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
